column1: Hi, I am a telecom professional, presently working as a senior manager in strategy & planning for a top-tier telecom MNC at Mumbai, India. I've had my schooling from prestigious schools in New Delhi, followed by B.E (Comp. Sc. Engg. ) with Distinction from Pune University. I'm pretty ambitious,and a solid go-getter, but since I like having my cake and eating it too, I try and maintain that elusive work-life balance. I grew up in Delhi, and have also lived extensively in Pune and Bangalore, before zeroing in on the wonderful, enterprising, chaotic, melting-pot of a metropolis that is Mumbai. I'm passionate about travel, literature, music, the feminist/humanist cause, yoga and nature. I'm a history buff, a feminist and a classical music enthusiast. I like theater, old films, world cinema and while I love my own company too, I suppose I could be called an extrovert as I also like meeting and engaging with like-minded passionate people. I also love exploring different cultures and places around the world and in India.. a sort of female Indiana Jones, if you will. I'm looking for a suitable, intellectual, well-educated, cultured person from a similar family upbringing, background & position. Looking for adventurous souls who are liberal, feminist, spiritual, devoid of ANY gender bias, and are blessed with a great sense of humor. Vegetarianism and being a non-smoker are key preferences.,"We are looking for a suitable, well-educated, cultured person from a similar family upbringing, background & position.

A well-traveled person brought up with liberal ideas and thoughts, a strong sense of ethics, a spirit of kindness and an interest in giving back to society, with an ability to relate to people well. A great sense of humor, varied interests and hobbies, a keen interest in different cultures & places, a broad-minded, independent, non-chauvinistic nature, and a cheerful disposition rounds off the ""list"". I usually get along best with creative, spiritual, intellectual, passionate, driven people, ideally interested in classical music, old temples, theater, art and good literature (that's how I spend most of my free time, hence I'd prefer someone whose interests match mine, else there wouldn't be any ""us"" time at all). Oh, and those who've grown up devouring the adventures of Bertram Wooster, Captain Haddock and folks from a certain Gaulish village usually end up being kindred spirits. Finally, vegetarianism, being a non-smoker, and being a feminist/devoid of all gender-bias, are must-haves. ","We come from a very well-placed, highly-educated family of senior-management PSU executives, and senior bureaucrats (IAS /IES) in the central government at New Delhi. My dad - an engineer from IIT-Madras, retired as a senior executive from a central PSU, New Delhi. Mom -a very well-known exponent of Indian classical music (the veena). My parents are currently based in Bangalore post retirement. My grandfather was a PadmaShree awardee, and a key adviser & Constitutional expert in the Central Govt. My sister - a Sr. Management professional at a leading software MNC in Mumbai, and bro-in-law, the MD & Head of Research(investment banking) at a global banking conglomerate.

column1:
Well, describing me in a few words is impossible however this word, impossible, in itself says I'M-POSSIBLE. So lemme try dis out. 

I, after a LOT of cajoling(from parent/family) have agreed to visit a few matrimonial sites, looking for my Mr. Right.  I have a pleasing personality with a very fair complexion. I am heavy in body type and working out these days to tone down my body as my bro, whose Maj with Indian Army has made me realise the hazards of being over weight. 

I simply LOVE food and am a GOOD cook too(but not too keen to enter the kitchen). I love pets especially dogs, have 2 as of now.

One drawback in me is that am drop dead emotional, one who would cry if any animal dies in a movie or when guy gets the girl at the end of all the turmoil in Bollywood movies. 

I am excellent in my communication skills(kudos to my groomin for the BPO industry). I have had International exposure during my tenure in the BPOs wherein my profile made me interact with US cliental on hourly/daily basis. Am very confident of my attributes.
 
My family consists of my dad who is a retired business man(fond of yoga/alternative therapies), mumma who is an HOD(music & dance), eldest bro who is a Defence Employee, sis-in-law who works wid special children, elder bro who owns the business of marketing Solar Solutions.

That's about  me. Lemme see my LUCK here........,"Okay, here I go describing my Mr. Right...... He should be wearing a shining armour, riding on a black horse and should be carrying a shiny sword........ HAHAHAHAHA. NO NO NO

That is not wht am looking for in my future partner. I am CRAZZZYYY about Indian Army. So, I would prefer my partner to be from the same profession. If not here are some traits which should be present in you to be my MAN:
# he should atleast have moderate values, if not liberal.
# he should have ability to make people laugh or smile
# he should be someone I love talking with as when we grow old that is one thing which would be required the most
# he should be someone I can be friends with rather than being a lover or a wife.
# he doesnt have to be a drop dead handsome as they dont make good husbands(kidding). Seriously, am looking for someone who would just look good with me not someone who is every women's dream man
# he should have respect for elders and love for young ones
# he should be able to cook to stay alive for himself
In short, you have to be someone I can be myself rather than portraying to be someone esle.......

column1: I am born and brought up in Mumbai in a nuclear family and have spent most part of my childhood in Aamchi Mumbai with my two lil sisters. I've completed my Bachelors in Commerce from MMK College, Mumbai. Further, went on to complete my Masters in Commerce from University of Mumbai. Though, I also did intend to pursue a degree in MBA, I wasn't able to complete the same due to untimely death of my father in 2002. We did have some challenges during our growing up years but by the grace of God, all of us three sisters got on our feet and have managed to do quite well for ourselves. My family had also moved to USA for around ten years and I've also spent quite some time out there before they moved back to India for good. Professionally, am a banker and currently working with a MNC bank in Operational Risk team in Mumbai. Personally am a fun loving person & love to live each day as it comes. Though am a foodie by nature, I also try to keep myself active by working out and swimming. A typical Indian who is a movie buff and an ardent cricket fan. column1:
Helping others is the best feeling for many people. It gives them satisfaction and pleasure, and I am one of those people who feels immensely happy when she helps others. Doing anything for them, if I can, gives me a wonderful feeling. 
That was why I chose the profession of teaching. I love my work and spending time with my students and teaching them is one of the best things I do in a day. I would like to grow in my profession. However, I can leave my profession if my future family expects me to. I am not very career oriented and this will not be a problem for me. 
I get emotionally attached with people quickly which is not very good for me. Though some people return the same feeling, but many end up hurting me. Apart from that, I am very homely and can manage household work efficiently. 
My father is a Senior Technician in IOCL. My mother is a homemaker and all my siblings are happily married. 
Education wise also, I am quite qualified. I have done B.COM, M.COM, NTT and B.ED. All these degrees have not only made me professionally sound, but have also made me confident. 
I am traditional but I donAA?A?t mind modernity, if itAA?A?s healthy. This according to me is a very good quality to possess. 
When I am free, I cook and serve people. They like my cooking and even if they do not, I am quite open to suggestions. I like listening to music as it refreshes my mind.,"I want my partner to be very good and be decent by nature. This will help us in bonding with each other. I am sure if he is like that, he will seek a lot of respect from me. Apart from that, I want him to be a non-smoker and a non-drinker. This is because I donAA?A?t want him to have any bad habits which will create a nuisance in a family.

I donAA?A?t mind him being from any profession. All I desire for is a well-settled man with a good job. His family should be very good and they should accept me as I am. This will not only make them like me, but also make me very comfortable.
As I mentioned above I am not career oriented and will not mind if my future family wants me to leave my job. However, they should not try to dominate me, as I will not take that.
My family is well reputed in the society and we all are proud of it. I expect the same from my future family. They should have a good background, as my parents will prefer that.
I am very traditional as a person but I donAA?A?t mind modernity if it is for good. I have accepted many modern values and I am ready to accept the same in future as well.

Apart from all I need from him is his support so that we can spend the rest of our lives happily.",,34 to 41,05 Oct 1979,08:25:00,India,Faridabad,,,,Brahmin - Saryuparin,,,,,,Daughter,M.Com. (Commerce),"34 yrs, 5ft 5in,

column1:
I describe myself as a simple and soft spoken person who is friendly in nature. I have deep faith in god as he always guides me to the correct path in life. 
Presently I am not working anywhere but in I would like to see myself working in a good organization at a reputed position. Further, I do a lot of hard work to attain the top position in life. My main weakness is that I am very emotional and sometimes people take advantage of my emotional nature. The ones who are close to me never make fun of me or take advantage. Rather they always try to make me strong in order to face this world with confidence. 
My mother is a homemaker and father is a business man. I have two brothers, one of them is married and both of them are engrossed in business.
After completing my school education I did B Com from Delhi University and MCM from Bharati Vidyapeeth, Pune, and MBA through Correspondence.
There are very few friends in my life and I like to spend most of my time with them only. They are always there to support me and always encourage me in life to achieve the best. In my free time I like listening music and watching movies with my friends. I also like to plan outings and go to new places.,"I want to marry a man according to my choices. He should be an understanding person. He must understand me and my aspirations in life. He should be a simple person with a fun loving nature. This way both of us will get to know each other well.

My life partner should be a well educated person with a positive outlook towards life. He must look at life broadly. His family should have a good image in the society as it will be the major area of concern for my family as well, as they want me to get settled in a well mannered family.

I describe myself as a very honest person who has a very fun loving nature. I love to have fun and spread happiness all around. My nature also inculcates accepting challenges and living up to the expectations of others. Further I have a very optimistic point of view towards life and always find positivity in everything.

My mother is a homemaker and father has taken retirement from his profession, earlier he was working with Railway. I have three brothers, first one is working as a Mechanical Engineer with National India Limited, the other one is working as an IT officer in a Central Bank and the last one is currently preparing for IAS exams. 
After my school education, I completed my MBA from Symbiosis, B Ed from IEPM, Ghaziabad, B Sc from MMH, Ghaziabad, M Phil from CCS University, Meerut and currently Pursuing MA (Education) from CCS University, Meerut.
Life is incomplete without friends as they are the best part of our life. I have very few friends and I like to be with them. Whenever I am free, I like to listen to music and watch movies. Further I also like to travel to new places and explore new things about every place. column1: I am settled in the United States of America and I am US citizen. I have Master's Degree from India in Commerce majoring in Business Administration from Pune University and earned three associate degrees in Computer Information Technology in America. I grew up in Pune, Maharashtra, India and I am presently settled in Michigan, USA. Personality wise, I would describe myself as a simple loving girl who belongs to middle class family. I am never married, understanding, caring, and homely person. My interests are healthy vegetarian cooking, gardening, landscaping, listening to music, and photography. Having been raised in India and living in the US for few years, I believe that I have a pretty decent mix of eastern and western cultures. My parents live with me and I prefer a man who will accept my parents, as I am only daughter to my parents. I fluently speak and understand Sindhi, English, Hindi. If you are mature and understanding please communicate directly. I am looking for any educated, Hindu professional, who maybe a doctor, engineer, any other professional who is well settled either in India or USA. Preference will given to Sindhi, Hindu boy. Prefer a boy who is settled or willing to settle in America. I can accept the boy who has any type of visa green card, H1B for USA.
